{
 "name": "RPlog_Drew_Makes_a_Stand",
 "title": "Drew Makes a Stand",
 "summary": "At Talon Karrde's base on Myrkr, the spacer Drew seeks out her partner, the mechanic Orson, to confront him over his decision to shelter the fugitive Jedi Simon Sezirok and Jessalyn against the wishes of Karrde and the danger it brings down on everyone. Drew presses Orson to admit he has no plan and to protect himself, while Orson insists that helping the Jedi was simply right, a matter of keeping his head and his heart as friends, even if it costs him everything, including Karrde's organization and any chance of finding the Death Star. Simon and Jessalyn, returning from a run, hesitate at the door and then enter mid-argument, the wounded Simon standing guard while Jessalyn awkwardly broaches the group's next move. Drew, shamed by Orson's stubborn idealism and shaken because part of her agrees with him, repeatedly tries to storm out only to be tripped up by his cluttered floor, while Orson pleads that he needs her to help him think. Learning belatedly of the injuries Drew suffered fleeing the New Republic, Orson apologizes, but neither will yield: he won't compromise his beliefs and she won't pretend that won't get him killed. The standoff ends unresolved, with Drew promising only to think it over before walking out, angry and embarrassed.",
